â€¢â€¢ImagesÂ°Â°
1. Most images and Background images should be applied with CSS.

2. The main method used for images are both the <img> tag with the src attribute referencing an image resource. Then the <alt> attribute describing the image.
â€¢â€¢Example:
<img src="images/Pic.png" alt="Eve">

3. Using the <srcset> attribute, enables providing multiple image for your project.
â€¢â€¢Example:
<img src="images/Pic.png" alt="Pic"
  srcset="images/Pic.png 400w, images/Pic-xl.jpg 800w"
  sizes="(max-width: 800px) 400px, 800px" />

4. Now a different option using the <picture> and <source> tags.
â€¢â€¢Example2:
<picture>
  <source src="images/Pic.png" media="(max-width: 800px)" />
  <source src="images/Pic-xl.jpg" />
  <img src="images/Pic.png" alt="Pic" />
</picture>

5. Both the <img> tag, & <input type="image">, can include height and width attributes.

6. We can use the <svg> tag for SVG Images and Extensions.

7. The <figure> element, along with  the <figcaption> element, can enable a image to include a description.

8. The src file is the path and filename of a embedded image. 

9. Example of <alt> text.
<img src="path/filename" alt="descriptive text" />

9Â¹. If it is a SVG Image:
<img src="switch.svg" alt="light switch" role="img" />

10. "<source> attributes" include srcset, sizes, media, width, and height.

11. Lazy loading.â€¢Â°âœ¨
â€¢â€¢This mechanism tells the Browser how to load the image.
â€¢â€¢ The default <eager> value means the image is loaded instantly as the HTML is <parsed>.
â€¢â€¢ By setting <loading="lazy"> the image loading is deferred until it  comes into the viewport. 
â€¢â€¢Example:
<img src="switch.svg" alt="light switch" loading="lazy" />


12.Aspect Ratio
â€¢â€¢As CSS is usually included in the <head>, it is parsed before any <img> is encountered.
â€¢â€¢Example Height & Width RatioÂ°Â°
<img src="switch.svg" alt="light switch" role="img" width="70" height="112" />


13. The <img> element also can support {ismap, crossorigin, decoding, referrerpolicy, in Blink-based browsers, fetchpriority attributes.} 

14. Example Response when a image is submitted with the x and y tags:
&imageSubmitName.x=169&imageSubmitName.y=66 

